{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-21T17:53:23.733Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "The learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the most critical hyperparameter in gradient descent and all neural network optimization—it controls the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "step size"}, {"type": "text", "text": " when updating model parameters, determining how aggressively the model learns from data. Finding the right learning rate is essential: too small causes painfully slow training, while too large causes the model to diverge and fail completely, making it the key to balancing speed, stability, and convergence in Generative AI training."}]}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Learning Rate — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it is — Clear definition and intuition"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical definition:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "learning rate η"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (eta) is a scaling factor that multiplies the gradient in the parameter update rule:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "θ_new = θ_old - η × ∇J(θ)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "θ"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = model parameters (weights, biases)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "η"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = learning rate (step size)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "∇J(θ)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = gradient of the loss function\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Negative sign"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = move opposite to gradient (downhill)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Intuitive analogy:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Imagine walking down a mountain blindfolded:\n\nη = 0.001 → Tiny steps (safe but painfully slow)\nη = 0.01 → Normal walking pace (good balance)\nη = 1.0 → Giant leaps (dangerous, might overshoot the valley)\n\nThe learning rate determines how far you step downhill each time [web:268][web:269]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key insight:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate controls optimization speed"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Large η → Fast progress across loss surface (but may overshoot)\n- Small η → Slow, careful progress (but may never converge)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why the learning rate matters — Impact on Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The learning rate directly affects:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Too Small (η = 0.0001)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Too Large (η = 1.0)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimal (η = 0.01)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Speed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Extremely slow convergence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast initially, then diverges"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast, stable"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Convergence"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "May never reach minimum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Oscillates or diverges"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Smooth convergence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Training time"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Days/weeks wasted"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model fails immediately"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Hours/days"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "GPU cost"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Expensive (long training)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Waste compute (failure)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Efficient"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Real example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Training GPT-4 with η = 0.00001 would take months; with η = 1.0 it would fail in minutes; with η = 0.001 it trains in weeks."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learning rate effects — Detailed analysis"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small Learning Rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (η = 0.0001)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Convergence behavior:\nIteration 1: θ = 5, gradient = 10, θ_new = 5 - 0.0001×10 = 4.999\nIteration 2: θ = 4.999, gradient = 10, θ_new = 4.999 - 0.0001×10 = 4.998\n...\nIteration 10000: θ ≈ 4.0 (barely moved!)\n\nProblems:\n→ Extremely slow convergence (takes forever) [web:268]\n→ May get stuck in local minima (can't \"jump\" over them) [web:268]\n→ Excessive GPU/compute cost [web:268]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large Learning Rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (η = 1.0)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Convergence behavior:\nIteration 1: θ = 5, gradient = 10, θ_new = 5 - 1×10 = -5\nIteration 2: θ = -5, gradient = -10, θ_new = -5 - 1×(-10) = 5\nIteration 3: θ = 5, gradient = 10, θ_new = 5 - 1×10 = -5\n...\nResult: Oscillates forever, never converges!\n\nProblems:\n→ Overshoots minimum [web:268]\n→ Diverges (loss increases instead of decreases) [web:268][web:270]\n→ Model fails completely [web:268]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimal Learning Rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (η = 0.01)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Convergence behavior:\nIteration 1: θ = 5, gradient = 10, θ_new = 5 - 0.01×10 = 4.9\nIteration 2: θ = 4.9, gradient = 9, θ_new = 4.9 - 0.01×9 = 4.81\nIteration 3: θ = 4.81, gradient = 8, θ_new = 4.81 - 0.01×8 = 4.73\n...\nIteration ∞: gradient ≈ 0 → θ stops changing (converged!)\n\nBenefits:\n→ Fast, stable convergence [web:268]\n→ Smooth path to minimum [web:268]\n→ Efficient training [web:268]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why small learning rates cause slow convergence"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical explanation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Step size = η × ||∇J(θ)||\n\nWhen η is small:\n→ Step size is tiny (even with large gradients)\n→ Must take many steps to reach minimum\n\nExample:\nDistance to minimum = 100 units\nGradient = 10\nη = 0.0001 → Step = 0.0001 × 10 = 0.001\nSteps needed = 100 / 0.001 = 100,000 iterations!\n\nIf η = 0.01 → Step = 0.01 × 10 = 0.1\nSteps needed = 100 / 0.1 = 1,000 iterations (100× faster!)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Physical intuition:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You're at the top of a mountain (high loss):\n- Small η = walking 1 mm per step\n- Need 100,000 steps to reach bottom\n- Takes days/weeks\n\nOptimal η = running 10 meters per step\n- Need 1,000 steps to reach bottom\n- Takes hours"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why large learning rates cause divergence"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mathematical explanation:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "sql"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Loss function: J(θ) = θ² (simple bowl)\nMinimum at θ = 0\n\nGradient: ∇J(θ) = 2θ\n\nUpdate: θ_new = θ - η × 2θ = θ × (1 - 2η)\n\nConvergence requires: |1 - 2η| < 1\n\nIf η = 0.01:\nθ_new = θ × (1 - 0.02) = 0.98θ\nθ → 0 (converges) ✓\n\nIf η = 1.0:\nθ_new = θ × (1 - 2) = -θ\nθ oscillates: 5 → -5 → 5 → -5 (diverges) ✗\n\nIf η = 2.0:\nθ_new = θ × (1 - 4) = -3θ\nθ explodes: 5 → -15 → 45 → -135 (diverges faster) ✗"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Physical intuition:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "You're at the top of the mountain:\n- Large η = jumping 100 meters per step\n- Mountain is only 10 meters wide\n- You overshoot the valley and land on the opposite hill\n- Next step: you jump back to where you started\n- Result: you oscillate forever, never reaching the bottom"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Learning rate schedules"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Using a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fixed learning rate"}, {"type": "text", "text": " often leads to suboptimal convergence. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate schedules"}, {"type": "text", "text": " gradually decrease η over time to balance exploration and refinement."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why schedules work:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start high (η = 0.1):\n→ Fast exploration across loss surface\n→ Escape local minima\n→ Make large initial progress\n\nGradually decrease (η → 0.001):\n→ Fine-tuning near minimum\n→ Smooth convergence\n→ Avoid overshooting"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Constant Learning Rate"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η = 0.01 (fixed throughout training)\n\nPros: Simple, no tuning\nCons: Suboptimal (may overshoot or converge slowly) [web:266]\n\nDefault: Constant rate for each epoch [web:280]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step Decay (Time-based)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η(epoch) = η₀ / (1 + decay × epoch)\n\nReduce LR by factor (e.g., 10×) at fixed epochs\nExample:\n  Epoch 0-30: η = 0.1\n  Epoch 31-60: η = 0.01\n  Epoch 61-90: η = 0.001 [web:266]\n\nPros: Large steps early, fine-tuning later\nCons: Requires knowing when to decay [web:266]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Implementation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "def step_decay_lr(epoch, eta_0=0.1, decay=0.01):\n    return eta_0 / (1 + decay * epoch)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Exponential Decay"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η(epoch) = η₀ × exp(-decay × epoch)\n\nSmooth exponential decrease [web:280]\n\nPros: Automatic decay\nCons: Requires tuning decay parameter"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cosine Annealing"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "η(t) = η_min + (η_max - η_min) × (1 + cos(π × t/T)) / 2\n\nLR follows cosine curve from max to min over T epochs [web:266]\n\nPros: Smooth decay, often achieves better accuracy than step decay\nCons: Requires tuning T (total epochs)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Implementation"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\ndef cosine_annealing_lr(epoch, eta_max=0.1, eta_min=0.001, T=100):\n    return eta_min + (eta_max - eta_min) * (1 + np.cos(np.pi * epoch / T)) / 2"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning Rate Warmup"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Start with small η, increase to max, then decrease:\n\nη(t) = small → η_max → η_min\n\nPopularized by fast.ai; achieves same accuracy in fewer epochs [web:266]\n\nPros: Prevents early divergence, improves convergence\nCons: Adds complexity"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Why warmup works"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- Training starts with noisy gradients\n- Large initial η can cause divergence\n- Small warmup η prevents early instability\n- Then increase to max for fast progress\n- Then decay for fine-tuning"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptive Decay (Validation-based)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Evaluate validation set after each epoch\nReduce LR when validation loss change < threshold\n\nTends to give good convergence to local optima [web:263]\n\nPros: Automatic, adaptive to training progress\nCons: Requires validation set"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Typical learning rate values"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Model Type"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common η range"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple networks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.01 - 0.1"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Deep networks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.001 - 0.01"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Transformers (GPT)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.0001 - 0.001"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "CNNs (ResNet)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "0.01 - 0.1"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "[medium](https://medium.com/@kiranvutukuri/16-optimization-fundamentals-gradient-descent-in-ai-845f49095e33)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How to choose the learning rate"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning Rate Test (LR Finder)"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# PyTorch: Scan η from 0.0001 to 10\nfor eta in [0.0001, 0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1.0, 10.0]:\n    train_loss = train_epoch(model, eta)\n    print(f\"η = {eta}: Loss = {train_loss}\")\n\nPlot loss vs. η; choose η just before loss starts increasing"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Grid Search"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Try multiple values\netabetas = [0.0001, 0.001, 0.01, 0.1]\nfor eta in etas:\n    model = train_model(eta)\n    accuracy = evaluate(model)\n    print(f\"η = {eta}: Accuracy = {accuracy}\")\n\nChoose η with highest accuracy [web:268]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use Adaptive Methods"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Adam: Automatically adjusts η per parameter\noptimizer = torch.optim.Adam(model.parameters(), lr=0.001)\n\nBenefit: Less tuning needed, often works well with default η = 0.001 [web:268]"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "orderedList", "attrs": {"start": 1, "type": null}, "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learning rate η = step size"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Controls how far to move parameters each update"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Update rule"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": θ = θ - η × ∇J(θ)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too small (η = 0.0001)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Slow convergence, excessive GPU cost, may get stuck"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Too large (η = 1.0)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Overshoots minimum, oscillates, diverges, model fails"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Optimal (η = 0.01)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Fast, stable convergence"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Small η problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Step size = η × gradient is tiny; need many steps"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Large η problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Step overshoots valley, lands on opposite hill, oscillates"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Constant LR"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Simple but suboptimal (default)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Step decay"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": η = η₀ / (1 + decay × epoch); large early, small late"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Cosine annealing"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": η follows cosine curve; smooth decay, better accuracy"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Warmup"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Start small, increase to max, then decrease; prevents early divergence"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Adaptive methods"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adam adjusts η per parameter; less tuning needed"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For Generative AI, the learning rate is absolutely critical: training GPT-4, DALL-E, and Stable Diffusion requires careful LR tuning (typically 0.0001-0.001 for transformers), learning rate schedules (cosine annealing, warmup) to achieve optimal convergence, and adaptive methods (Adam) to reduce sensitivity to LR choice—making it the most important hyperparameter to master for successful AI training."}]}]}}